x4freetext: MEDIUM- AND HEAVY-WEIGHT NUCLEI IN THE KEV REGION.-
3 MV VAN DE GRAAFF ACCELERATOR, PULSED
AS TO YIELD WHITE SPECTRUM WITH USEFUL
TIME OF FLIGHT, 1.5 M PATH, 10 NS PULSES,
TO AN ENERGY RESOLUTION OF 2 PERCENT AT
800 L LIQUID SCINTILLATOR TANK. BOTH FLIGHT
TIME AND PULSE HEIGHT ARE RECORDED WITH
THRESHOLDS OF ABOUT 3 AND 1 MEV, RESP.
.RESONANCE-AVERAGE FORMALISM OF LANE AND LYNN WAS USED
TO DETERMINE NEUTRON (P-, D-WAVE) AND PHOTON STRENGTH
FUNCTIONS BY LEAST-SQUARES FIT TO CAPTURE X-SECTIONS.
S-WAVE STRENGTH FUNCTION WAS TAKEN FROM SETH S TABLE.
AS AVERAGE OVER 3 MEASUREMENTS RELATIVE TO
NORMALIZING SHAPE TO 596 MB AT 30 KEV.
THIS MEANS THAT ALL SIGMA(N,GAMMA) SHOULD BE
WERE APPLIED FOLLOWING MACKLIN. THEY NEVER EXCEEDED
8 PERCENT. OTHER CORRECTIONS WERE MADE FOR GAMMA RAY
ESCAPE FROM TANK (ABOUT 3 PERCENT), PULSE HEIGHT
SPECTRUM FRACTION BELOW ELECTRONIC THRESHOLD, AMBIENT
- ERROR IN REFERENCE CROSS SECTION        3-8 PERCENT
- UNCERT. IN REGISTERED SPECTRUM FRACTION  5  PERCENT
- UNCERT. IN CASCADE ESCAPE PROBABILITY    3  PERCENT
- UNCERT. SELF-SHIELD. AND MULT. SCATT.    1  PERCENT
.METAL DISC, 9 CM DIAMETER, ABOUT 0.1 CM THICKNESS.

3 MM THICK LI-6 GLASS DETECTOR WITH REL.
EFFICIENCY CALCULATED FROM CROSS SECTION FIT GIVEN
BY BERGSTROEM ET AL. IN CCDN-NW3 (1966) AND MULTIPLE
SCATTERING CORRECTIONS GIVEN BY ZETTERSTROEM ET AL.
0.025 ATOMS/BARN B-10 SLAB WITH REL. EFFIC.
CALCULATED FROM 1/V ABSORPTION CROSS SECTION FOR B-10
AND BRANCHING RATIO RECOMMENDED BY SPAEPEN, MULTIPLE
.THE SHAPE OF THE AU(N,GAMMA) X-SECTION WAS DETERMINED
AS A WEIGHTED AVERAGE OVER DATA TAKEN WITH THESE 2
DETECTORS AND ALSO WITH A GREY DETECTOR (POENITZ,
.THE ABSOLUTE VALUE WAS FIXED BY NORMALIZING THE SHAPE
TO 596+-12MB AT 30 KEV AS RECOMMENDED BY POENITZ ET
- UNCERT. IN REFERENCE CROSS SECTION SHAPES 5 PERC.
- UNCERT. IN NORMALIZATION AT 30 KEV ...... 3 PERC.
- UNCERT. IN MULT. SCATT. CORRECTIONS ..... 3 PERC.
- UNCERT. IN AIR SCATTERING DIFFERENCES ... 0.5 PERC.
- UNCERT. IN SPECTRUM FRACTION E-VARIAT. .. 4 PERC.
